author: @gna_bn_ahc
text:
How to make Felix's Brownies 
                
Ingredients:
1 cup (250g) unsalted butter, melted

2 cups (400g) sugar

1 cup (120g) cocoa powder

1 tsp vanilla extract

4 eggs

1 cup (125g) all-purpose flour

1/2 tsp salt

1/2 tsp baking powder

Optional: chocolate chips or nuts for extra texture

Instructions:

Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).

Melt the butter in a microwave-safe bowl or over the stove.

Mix sugar and cocoa: In a separate bowl, combine sugar and cocoa powder.

Add melted butter: Pour the melted butter into the sugar-cocoa mixture and stir well.

Add vanilla and eggs: Mix in the vanilla extract and then beat the eggs one by one into the batter until smooth.

Dry ingredients: In a separate bowl, whisk together the flour, salt, and baking powder. Gradually mix it into the wet ingredients.

Add-ins (optional): If you want, fold in chocolate chips or nuts to the mixture for some extra flavor and texture.

Bake: Pour the batter into a greased or parchment-lined 9x13-inch (23x33cm) baking pan. Spread it out evenly.

Bake for 25-30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out with a few moist crumbs (not completely dry).

Cool and serve: Let the brownies cool completely before cutting them into squares.

Enjoy your brownies!
